    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Trademarked name for a series of acrylic copolymer resins. They are applied to a wide range of object materials as an adhesive, consolidant, and protective coating. Paraloid (TM) resins are widely used in conservation treatments. Formerly marketed as Acryloid (TM) in the United States.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
